(186, 'Flower Totems', '\"Shin (neutral), Soi (sunny) and Tai (shady) are three essential components to Ikebana (Japanese Flower arranging).  The red forms are romantic, the blue calm and stoic, the yellow energetic\" (Excerpt from artist statement)', 'Sculpture', 'In place', 'Median', 'Kingsway & King Edward Ave', 'Steel', 'https://opendata.vancouver.ca/api/datasets/1.0/public-art/images/1009fa7a6bb38da4a0b586200bb8e27b', 'City of Vancouver', 'Kensington-Cedar Cottage', 'Centre of green space', '{\"type\": \"Point\", \"coordinates\": [-123.073144, 49.248619]}', 'Three steel vertical poles hold silhouettes of stylized flower forms enamelled in different primary colours.', 47, 1980),
(187, 'Untitled', 'The rock was imported from Cortes Island, the artist\'s home. The artist said, \"I like the tricks of handling it, the blocks and tackle and the jacks. A sculptor likes the balance.\" The work was inspired by the natural beach landscape, \"I saw these big timbers there rubbing, the rock and the beams together. I was more constructive, but on the beach is nothing like this, is absolute sculpture..sometimes only for one day, the next, the tide took it away and destroyed it already.\"(V.Sun, June 21, 1986)', 'Sculpture', 'Removed', 'Harbour Front Park', 'Main Street (north end)', 'Red cedar, boulder', 'https://opendata.vancouver.ca/api/datasets/1.0/public-art/images/087c9a2433898903bc132eccbb08aae9', 'City of Vancouver', 'Strathcona', 'West end of park', '', 'A structure of large cedar logs is inspired by Japanese architecture. A large black rock (that the artist calls a natural sculpture) sits in the centre of the work.', 137, 1986),
(188, 'Horizons', 'A private commission by F. Cameron Wilkinson to commemorate the 60th anniversary of the Wilkinson Company, a steel and metals distribution and procesing firm. The city planning department originally denied it a permit on the grounds that it viiolated a zoning bylaw forbidding structures in landscaped setbacks of industrial sites.  The company appealed the ruling and won.', 'Sculpture', 'In place', 'Wilkinson Company', '888 S.E. Marine Drive', 'Corten steel', 'https://opendata.vancouver.ca/api/datasets/1.0/public-art/images/fc77aa1806946fd5a6d04db5b766e8b3', 'private', 'Sunset', 'Lawn in front of bldg.', '{\"type\": \"Point\", \"coordinates\": [-123.087875, 49.210433]}', 'Three geometric hard-edge  forms of corten steel reach away from each other to narrow points. The sculpture weighs 7000 lbs. The surface weathers to a dark blue.', 41, 1970),
